  lang={lang}
  heroTitle="Privacy Policy"
  heroSubtitle="How we collect, use, and protect your personal data"
  lastUpdated="July 11, 2026"
  keywords="privacy policy, data protection, GDPR, Swiss DSG, personal data"
>
  <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
  <p>Emanuel Flury ("we", "us", or "our") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you visit our website eflury.com (the "Site").</p>

  <h2>2. Data Controller</h2>
  <p>The data controller responsible for your personal data is:</p>
  <div class="info-box">
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Name:</strong> eFlury Consulting, Emanuel Flury</li>
      <li><strong>Address:</strong> Keltenweg 4, 2540 Grenchen, Switzerland</li>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:me@eflury.com">me@eflury.com</a></li>
      <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+41799107787">+41 79 910 77 87</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2>3. Data We Collect</h2>
  <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Contact information (name, email, phone number)</li>
    <li>Messages sent through our contact form</li>
    <li>Your email address when you subscribe to our newsletter or download a guide</li>
    <li>Professional information for service inquiries</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Automatically Collected Information</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>IP address (anonymized)</li>
    <li>Browser type and version</li>
    <li>Device information</li>
    <li>Pages visited and time spent</li>
    <li>Referral source</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. How We Use Your Data</h2>
  <p>We use your personal data for the following purposes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Responding to your inquiries</li>
    <li>Sending our newsletter (only with your sign-up; unsubscribe anytime via the link in each email or by writing to us)</li>
    <li>Providing our consulting services</li>
    <li>Improving our website and services</li>
    <li>Sending relevant communications (with your consent)</li>
    <li>Complying with legal obligations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
  <p>Under the revised Swiss Data Protection Act (revDSG/FADP) and, where applicable, the GDPR, we process your data based on:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Consent:</strong> When you voluntarily provide information</li>
    <li><strong>Contract:</strong> To fulfill service agreements</li>
    <li><strong>Legitimate Interest:</strong> To improve our services and website</li>
    <li><strong>Legal Obligation:</strong> To comply with applicable laws</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Data Sharing — the services we use</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal data. The following named service providers process data on our behalf:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Hostinger</strong> — hosting of this website (EU)</li>
    <li><strong>HubSpot</strong> — processing of contact and newsletter form submissions and our customer database (EU data centre, Frankfurt; the provider is a US company certified under the Swiss–U.S. Data Privacy Framework, and certain service data may be processed in the USA)</li>
    <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — web statistics (Google, USA; transfers safeguarded per section 7)</li>
    <li><strong>Cloudflare Turnstile</strong> — spam protection on our forms; processes technical connection data (Cloudflare, USA; transfers safeguarded per section 7)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Beyond these, data may be shared with professional advisors (accountants, lawyers) and with authorities when legally required. This list matches the disclosure on our <a href="/en/trust/">Trust &amp; Security</a> page.</p>

  <h2>7. International Transfers</h2>
  <p>Some of the providers above are US companies, so personal data may be transferred to the USA. Switzerland recognizes an adequate level of protection for US companies certified under the Swiss–U.S. Data Privacy Framework (in force since 15 September 2024); for providers or cases not covered by that certification, we rely on Standard Contractual Clauses.</p>

  <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>We retain your data only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this policy, or as required by law. Contact data is typically retained for 3 years after your last interaction.</p>

  <h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>Under Swiss and EU data protection laws, you have the right to:</p>
  <div class="info-box">
    <ul>
      <li>Access your personal data</li>
      <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
      <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
      <li>Restrict processing</li>
      <li>Data portability</li>
      <li>Object to processing</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:me@eflury.com">me@eflury.com</a>.</p>

  <h2>10. Cookies</h2>
  <p>Our website uses cookies. For detailed information, please see our <a href="/en/cookies/">Cookie Policy</a>.</p>

  <h2>11. Security</h2>
  <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data, including encryption, secure servers, and regular security assessments.</p>

  <h2>12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this privacy policy periodically. We will notify you of significant changes by posting the new policy on this page.</p>

  <h2>13. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>For questions about this privacy policy or our data practices:</p>
  <div class="info-box">
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:me@eflury.com">me@eflury.com</a></li>
      <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+41799107787">+41 79 910 77 87</a></li>
      <li><strong>Address:</strong> Grenchen, Switzerland</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2>14. Supervisory Authority</h2>
  <p>You have the right to lodge a complaint with the Federal Data Protection and Information Commissioner (FDPIC) in Switzerland or your local data protection authority.</p>
</ContentPageLayout>
